/www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/PhilCollinsnot-hungry-new-music-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/PhilCollinsnot-hungry-new-music-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/PhilCollinsnot-hungry-new-music-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/PhilCollinsnot-hungry-new-music-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/phil-collins">Phil Collins</a> has said he is “not hungry” enough to make any new music.</p><p> The soloist and former <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/genesis">Genesis</a> singer/drummer hasn&#39;t released an album of original music since Disney&#39;s <em>Brother Bear</em> soundtrack in 2003. His seventh and latest solo record, &#39;Testify&#39;, arrived the previous year. In 2010, he shared an LP of Mowtown and soul covers titled &#39;Going Back&#39;.</p><p> Collins has been suffering from health issues in recent years, following a spinal injury back in 2007. At <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-genesis-play-last-ever-gig-in-london-after-tonight-weve-all-gotta-get-real-jobs-3191470">Genesis&#39; final shows in 2022</a> , he performed from a chair while his son Nic took on drum duties. He also uses a cane to help him walk.</p><p> However, it was reported last summer that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/phil-collins-shares-health-update-i-feel-like-ive-used-up-my-air-miles-3823663">Collins was working on new music for the first time in over two decades</a> after having his studio revamped. This update came from producer and journalist Simon Napier-Bell, who posted an image of himself with Collins.</p><p> “For sure, before too long we&#39;re going to hear some new music,” he wrote in the caption (see below). </p><div id="fb-root"></div><p><script async="1" defer="1" crossorigin="anonymous" src="https://connect.facebook.net/en_US/sdk.js#xfbml=1&amp;version=v22.0"></script></p><div class="fb-post" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/simonnapierbell/posts/pfbid02yJgLniL3yR6anZ9Kj83cchH13Sta9NwWEbEV5aWGbJpRmVQqT242koM8Zh9L8ffFl?ref=embed_post" data-width="696"><blockquote cite="https://graph.facebook.com/100063636764382/posts/1085981303533085/" class="fb-xfbml-parse-ignore"><p> THE MARQUEE MOVIE…Yesterday we filmed Phil Collins at his house by Lake Geneva. He was in top form, full of wicked…</p><p> Posted by <a href="https://www.facebook.com/simonnapierbell">Simon Napier-Bell</a> on <a href="https://graph.facebook.com/100063636764382/posts/1085981303533085/">Monday, August 19, 2024</a></p></blockquote></div><p> But in a new interview for <a href="https://www.mojo4music.com/articles/stories/phil-collins-im-not-hungry-for-it-anymore/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>MOJO</em></a> &#39;s April issue, Collins revealed that he currently does not have the appetite to create amid ongoing struggles with his health.</p><p> “I keep thinking I should go downstairs to the studio and see what happens,” he told the magazine. “But I&#39;m not hungry for it anymore. The thing is, I&#39;ve been sick, I mean <em>very</em> sick.”</p><p> Elsewhere in the chat, Collins remembered responding to the advert Genesis had posted in <em>Melody Maker</em> after the departure of their third drummer John Mayhew.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/phil-collins-shares-health-update-i-feel-like-ive-used-up-my-air-miles-3823663">Collins previously gave an update on his health</a> during an interview for his 2024 documentary <em>…Drummer First</em> – though the conversation had been recorded two years prior.</p><p> He said: “If I wake up one day and I can hold a pair of drumsticks, then I&#39;ll have a crack of it. But I just feel like I&#39;ve used up my air miles. It&#39;s still kind of sinking in a bit… I&#39;ve spent all my life playing drums. To be suddenly not be able to do that is a shock.”</p><p> The interview was accompanied by <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-phil-collins-test-out-his-classic-drum-kit-in-over-a-decade-3825025">a video of Collins being reunited with his classic Gretsch drum kit</a> – which had been in storage for over a decade.</p><p> In early 2023, ex-Genesis guitarist and bassist Mike Rutherford explained that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/phil-collins-is-much-more-immobile-than-he-used-to-be-says-genesis-bandmate-in-health-update-3410857">Collins was “much more immobile than he used to be”</a> and was “enjoying his time at home”.</p><p> Last September, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/phil-collins-announces-both-sides-30th-anniversary-box-set-with-demos-and-rarities-3774630">Collins released a 30th anniversary box set of his 1993 album &#39;Both Sides&#39;</a> .</p><p> In 2022, Collins&#39; daughter and <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/emily-in-paris"><em>Emily In Paris</em></a> star <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/lily-collins-pays-tribute-to-dad-phil-collins-after-final-genesis-performance-3191997">Lily paid tribute to her father</a> after <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-genesis-play-last-ever-gig-in-london-after-tonight-weve-all-gotta-get-real-jobs-3191470">Genesis performed their final-ever live show together at The O2 in London</a> . “Tonite marks the end of an era,” she wrote.</p><p> “To have witnessed this last show was truly the memory of a lifetime and an event I shall hold in my heart forever.” She went on to thank Genesis “for the memories”, and called her dad “such an inspiration”.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/phil-collins-says-hes-not-hungry-enough-to-make-new-music-3840210">Phil Collins says he&#39;s “not hungry enough” to make new music</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
